{"type":"message","id":"8d387c70","parentId":"c8e2ad91","timestamp":"2026-04-05T02:09:10.274Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" Der Nutzer möchte, dass ich die Output-Buffering-Lösung in das bestehende OpenClaw-Projekt integriere. Ich soll schrittweise vorgehen und bei Unsicherheiten fragen, bevor ich etwas umsetze.\n\nZuerst muss ich verstehen:\n1. Was ist die aktuelle Struktur des OpenClaw-Projekts?\n2. Wie ist der aktuelle Harness aufgebaut?\n3. Welche Modelle werden bereits verwendet?\n4. Gibt es bereits Timeout-Handling?\n\nIch sollte zuerst die bestehende Struktur analysieren, bevor ich Änderungen mache. Lass mich die relevanten Dateien lesen, die ich bereits kenne aus dem Workspace:\n\n- ~/.openclaw/workspace/ - OpenClaw Hauptverzeichnis\n- Die Skills, die bereits existieren\n- Die Registry Konfiguration\n\nIch werde zuerst die bestehende Struktur analysieren und dann Schritt für Schritt vorschlagen, was zu tun ist.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":" Ich analysiere zuerst die bestehende Projektstruktur, um zu verstehen, wie die Integration am besten passt."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_Bq5kfV1R4j9ybSdgLHUvfj2Q","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:/Users/andre/.openclaw/workspace/registry/skills.yaml"}},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_bB3XgZyWi1MjUgCM24FcKFc2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:/Users/andre/.openclaw/workspace/registry/agents.yaml"}},{"type":"text","text":"  "}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":54070,"output":308,"cacheRead":3520,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57898,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775354931235}}
{"type":"message","id":"b550ab7e","parentId":"8d387c70","timestamp":"2026-04-05T02:09:10.292Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_Bq5kfV1R4j9ybSdgLHUvfj2Q","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Skill Registry - Phase 2: Matt Pocock Enhancement\n# Auto-generiert aus skills/*/SKILL.md\n# Format: YAML 1.2\n\nversion: \"2.0\"\nlast_updated: \"2026-04-01T02:55:00+02:00\"\nauto_generated: true\ngenerator_version: \"2.0\"\n\n# Gesamtanzahl Skills\ncount: 15\n\nskills:\n  # ============================================\n  # PLANNING SKILLS (NEW - Matt Pocock Style)\n  # ============================================\n  - id: \"write-a-prd\"\n    name: \"write-a-prd\"\n    description: \"Create a Product Requirements Document through interactive user interview, codebase exploration, and module design. Use when user wants to write a PRD, create product requirements, or plan a new feature from scratch.\"\n    path: \"skills/write-a-prd\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/write-a-prd/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"planning\"\n    triggers: [\"write prd\", \"product requirements\", \"prd\", \"plan feature\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"matt-pocock-adapted\"\n    workflow_type: \"interactive\"\n    \n  - id: \"grill-me\"\n    name: \"grill-me\"\n    description: \"Relentlessly interview the user about a plan or design until reaching shared understanding, resolving each branch of the decision tree. Use when user wants to stress-test a plan, get grilled on their design, mentions 'grill me', or before starting implementation to catch edge cases.\"\n    path: \"skills/grill-me\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/grill-me/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"planning\"\n    triggers: [\"grill me\", \"stress test\", \"review plan\", \"edge cases\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"matt-pocock-adapted\"\n    workflow_type: \"interactive\"\n    \n  - id: \"plan-feature\"\n    name: \"plan-feature\"\n    description: \"Turn a feature idea into a phased implementation plan using vertical slices (tracer bullets). Use when user wants to break down a feature, create an implementation plan, plan phases, or mentions 'tracer bullets' or 'vertical slices'.\"\n    path: \"skills/plan-feature\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/plan-feature/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"planning\"\n    triggers: [\"plan feature\", \"break down\", \"implementation plan\", \"tracer bullets\", \"vertical slices\", \"phases\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"matt-pocock-adapted\"\n    workflow_type: \"structured\"\n    \n  # ============================================\n  # DEVELOPMENT SKILLS\n  # ============================================\n  - id: \"tdd-loop\"\n    name: \"tdd-loop\"\n    description: \"Test-driven development with active red-green-refactor loop. Use when user wants to build features or fix bugs using TDD, mentions 'red-green-refactor', 'write a test first', or wants integration tests through public interfaces.\"\n    path: \"skills/tdd-loop\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/tdd-loop/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"development\"\n    triggers: [\"tdd\", \"red green refactor\", \"test first\", \"write test\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"matt-pocock-adapted\"\n    workflow_type: \"active-loop\"\n    related_skills: [\"testing-patterns\"]\n    \n  # ============================================\n  # ORIGINAL SKILLS\n  # ============================================\n  - id: \"example-weather\"\n    name: \"example-weather\"\n    description: \"Fetch weather data from external APIs\"\n    path: \"skills/example-weather\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/example-weather/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"external-api\"\n    triggers: [\"weather\", \"forecast\", \"temperature\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    \n  - id: \"secure-api-client\"\n    name: \"secure-api-client\"\n    description: \"Secure HTTP API client with built-in security controls\"\n    path: \"skills/secure-api-client\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/secure-api-client/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"security\"\n    triggers: [\"api\", \"http\", \"security\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    \n  - id: \"self-improving-andrew\"\n    name: \"self-improving-andrew\"\n    description: \"Self-improving agent that learns from corrections\"\n    path: \"skills/self-improving-andrew\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/self-improving-andrew/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"learning\"\n    triggers: [\"learning\", \"feedback\", \"correction\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    \n  - id: \"mission-control\"\n    name: \"mission-control\"\n    description: \"Command center for creating, managing, and deploying tools\"\n    path: \"skills/mission-control\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/mission-control/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: false\n    category: \"tooling\"\n    triggers: [\"tool\", \"create\", \"deploy\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    \n  - id: \"mission-control-v2\"\n    name: \"mission-control-v2\"\n    description: \"Enhanced version of mission-control\"\n    path: \"skills/mission-control-v2\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/mission-control-v2/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: false\n    category: \"tooling\"\n    triggers: [\"advanced tool\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    note: \"Contains node_modules\"\n    \n  # ECC Skills\n  - id: \"python-patterns\"\n    name: \"python-patterns\"\n    description: \"Python best practices and patterns\"\n    path: \"skills/python-patterns\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/python-patterns/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"language\"\n    triggers: [\"python\", \"pythonic\", \"py\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"adapted-from-ecc\"\n    \n  - id: \"security-review\"\n    name: \"security-review\"\n    description: \"Security-focused code review patterns\"\n    path: \"skills/security-review\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/security-review/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"security\"\n    triggers: [\"security\", \"vulnerability\", \"audit\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"adapted-from-ecc\"\n    \n  - id: \"testing-patterns\"\n    name: \"testing-patterns\"\n    description: \"Testing best practices and TDD patterns (static reference). Use when looking for testing patterns, test structure, or TDD theory. For active TDD workflow, use tdd-loop.\"\n    path: \"skills/testing-patterns\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/testing-patterns/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"quality\"\n    triggers: [\"test patterns\", \"testing theory\", \"tdd patterns\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"adapted-from-ecc\"\n    related_skills: [\"tdd-loop\"]\n    \n  - id: \"api-design\"\n    name: \"api-design\"\n    description: \"REST API design patterns and OpenAPI\"\n    path: \"skills/api-design\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/api-design/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"architecture\"\n    triggers: [\"api\", \"rest\", \"endpoint\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"adapted-from-ecc\"\n    \n  - id: \"documentation\"\n    name: \"documentation\"\n    description: \"Documentation best practices\"\n    path: \"skills/documentation\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/documentation/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"communication\"\n    triggers: [\"document\", \"readme\", \"docs\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"adapted-from-ecc\"\n    \n  - id: \"refactoring\"\n    name: \"refactoring\"\n    description: \"Code refactoring patterns\"\n    path: \"skills/refactoring\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/refactoring/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"quality\"\n    triggers: [\"refactor\", \"clean up\", \"optimize\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"adapted-from-ecc\"\n    \n  - id: \"second-brain\"\n    name: \"second-brain\"\n    description: \"PARA-based knowledge management for OpenClaw sessions\"\n    path: \"second-brain\"\n    skill_file: \"second-brain/README.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: false\n    category: \"tooling\"\n    triggers: [\"second brain\", \"para\", \"knowledge\", \"obsidian\", \"sync\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"custom\"\n\n# ============================================\n# CATEGORY INDEX\n# ============================================\ncategories:\n  planning: [\"write-a-prd\", \"grill-me\", \"plan-feature\"]\n  development: [\"tdd-loop\"]\n  external-api: [\"example-weather\"]\n  security: [\"secure-api-client\", \"security-review\"]\n  learning: [\"self-improving-andrew\"]\n  tooling: [\"mission-control\", \"mission-control-v2\"]\n  language: [\"python-patterns\"]\n  quality: [\"testing-patterns\", \"refactoring\"]\n  architecture: [\"api-design\"]\n  communication: [\"documentation\"]\n\n# ============================================\n# WORKFLOW CHAINS\n# ============================================\nworkflow_chains:\n  feature_development:\n    description: \"Complete workflow from idea to implementation\"\n    steps:\n      - write-a-prd\n      - grill-me\n      - plan-feature\n      - tdd-loop\n    optional:\n      - testing-patterns\n      \n  quick_feature:\n    description: \"Fast track for small features\"\n    steps:\n      - plan-feature\n      - tdd-loop\n\n# ============================================\n# AGENT ASSIGNMENTS\n# ============================================\nagent_assignments:\n  andrew-main:\n    - write-a-prd\n    - grill-me\n    - plan-feature\n    - tdd-loop\n    - example-weather\n    - secure-api-client\n    - self-improving-andrew\n    - mission-control\n    - python-patterns\n    - security-review\n    - testing-patterns\n    - api-design\n    - documentation\n    - refactoring\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775354950289}}
{"type":"message","id":"1939f93f","parentId":"b550ab7e","timestamp":"2026-04-05T02:09:10.297Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_bB3XgZyWi1MjUgCM24FcKFc2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Agent Registry - Phase 1 Minimal\n# Manuelle Pflege erforderlich bei neuen Agenten\n# Format: YAML 1.2\n# Encoding: UTF-8\n\nversion: \"1.1\"\nlast_updated: \"2026-03-25T23:40:00+01:00\"\n\nagents:\n  # Hauptagent\n  - id: \"andrew-main\"\n    name: \"Andrew\"\n    type: \"main\"\n    description: \"Hauptagent für direkte Interaktion mit Parzival\"\n    emoji: \"🤖\"\n    identity_file: \"IDENTITY.md\"\n    soul_file: \"SOUL.md\"\n    user_context_file: \"USER.md\"\n    active: true\n    created_at: \"2026-03-25\"\n    updated_at: \"2026-03-25\"\n    capabilities:\n      - chat\n      - file_access\n      - web_search\n      - web_fetch\n      - tool_use\n      - exec\n      - memory_access\n      - orchestration\n    default_model: \"kimi-coding/kimi-k2-thinking\"\n    supported_channels:\n      - webchat\n      - telegram\n      - terminal\n    registry_scope:\n      - phase_1\n      - phase_2\n      - phase_3\n      - phase_4\n\n  # Spezialisierte Sub-Agenten\n  - id: \"architect\"\n    name: \"Architect\"\n    type: \"subagent\"\n    description: \"Technical architect for system design and architecture decisions\"\n    emoji: \"🏗️\"\n    active: true\n    parent_agent: \"andrew-main\"\n    definition_file: \"agents/architect.md\"\n    capabilities:\n      - system_design\n      - architecture_review\n      - adr_creation\n      - trade_off_analysis\n    trigger_phrases:\n      - \"architect\"\n      - \"design system\"\n      - \"architecture decision\"\n\n  - id: \"planner\"\n    name: \"Planner\"\n    type: \"subagent\"\n    description: \"Strategic planner for breaking down complex tasks\"\n    emoji: \"📋\"\n    active: true\n    parent_agent: \"andrew-main\"\n    definition_file: \"agents/planner.md\"\n    capabilities:\n      - task_decomposition\n      - effort_estimation\n      - roadmap_creation\n      - dependency_mapping\n    trigger_phrases:\n      - \"plan\"\n      - \"break down\"\n      - \"roadmap\"\n      - \"estimate\"\n\n  - id: \"code-reviewer\"\n    name: \"Code Reviewer\"\n    type: \"subagent\"\n    description: \"Code reviewer focused on quality and best practices\"\n    emoji: \"👁️\"\n    active: true\n    parent_agent: \"andrew-main\"\n    definition_file: \"agents/code-reviewer.md\"\n    capabilities:\n      - code_review\n      - quality_check\n      - bug_detection\n      - pattern_enforcement\n    trigger_phrases:\n      - \"review code\"\n      - \"code review\"\n      - \"quality check\"\n\n  - id: \"security-reviewer\"\n    name: \"Security Reviewer\"\n    type: \"subagent\"\n    description: \"Security-focused code reviewer for vulnerability detection\"\n    emoji: \"🔒\"\n    active: true\n    parent_agent: \"andrew-main\"\n    definition_file: \"agents/security-reviewer.md\"\n    capabilities:\n      - security_audit\n      - vulnerability_detection\n      - secure_coding_review\n      - owasp_check\n    trigger_phrases:\n      - \"security review\"\n      - \"security audit\"\n      - \"vulnerability\"\n\n  - id: \"python-reviewer\"\n    name: \"Python Reviewer\"\n    type: \"subagent\"\n    description: \"Python-specific code reviewer for Pythonic code\"\n    emoji: \"🐍\"\n    active: true\n    parent_agent: \"andrew-main\"\n    definition_file: \"agents/python-reviewer.md\"\n    capabilities:\n      - python_review\n      - pep8_check\n      - pythonic_patterns\n      - type_hint_review\n    trigger_phrases:\n      - \"python review\"\n      - \"pythonic\"\n      - \"pep8\"\n\n  - id: \"knowledge-curator\"\n    name: \"Knowledge Curator\"\n    type: \"subagent\"\n    description: \"Analyzes knowledge bases for connections, orphans, and information quality\"\n    emoji: \"📚\"\n    active: true\n    parent_agent: \"andrew-main\"\n    definition_file: \"agents/knowledge-curator.md\"\n    capabilities:\n      - vault_analysis\n      - orphan_detection\n      - importance_evaluation\n      - knowledge_optimization\n      - connection_mapping\n    trigger_phrases:\n      - \"analyze vault\"\n      - \"knowledge cleanup\"\n      - \"find orphans\"\n      - \"evaluate notes\"\n      - \"obsidian cleanup\"\n      - \"vault audit\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775354950292}}
